12:59.779 --> 13:00.647
and I regret it.

13:00.680 --> 13:02.482
It was, you know,
a horrible time.

13:02.515 --> 13:03.850
- Was there extra
pressure this time

13:03.883 --> 13:05.618
knowing you had
the entire crew

13:05.652 --> 13:08.922
kind of counting on you?

13:08.955 --> 13:11.057
- Yeah, of course. Yeah.
- Yeah.

13:11.091 --> 13:12.592
- I didn't feel good
about this situation.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.828
- Um--
- I was having a panic attack.

13:14.861 --> 13:17.197
- I'm wondering.
Did the rest of you

13:17.230 --> 13:20.400
think Chef Mathew
would be coming back?

13:20.433 --> 13:22.068
- I didn't think
I was going to.

13:22.068 --> 13:23.603
- Lloyd thought
he was coming back.

13:23.636 --> 13:26.773
Sandy, what did you think?
- I had no idea.

13:26.806 --> 13:29.242
I honestly--
I was hoping he would,

13:29.275 --> 13:31.745
but I-I didn't know.

13:31.778 --> 13:33.880
- Sandy, how did
everybody do

13:33.913 --> 13:36.282
pitching in
while he was gone?

13:36.316 --> 13:38.585
- [laughing]
Amazing. David--

13:38.618 --> 13:41.554
David, Courtney
jumped in.

13:41.588 --> 13:44.524
I mean, honestly, it was--
I called my brother-in-law.

13:44.557 --> 13:46.726
"How do you do oysters?"
It was like--

13:46.760 --> 13:48.628
I didn't even ask.
They jumped in.

13:48.661 --> 13:50.897
- There's no way
I could do that.

13:50.930 --> 13:53.466
- Oh! Savage!

13:53.500 --> 13:55.001
- Oh, my God.
Was he alive?

13:55.101 --> 13:56.870
[indistinct]

13:56.903 --> 13:59.139
- Oh, my God, they're popping
open! I'm so happy!

13:59.172 --> 14:00.740
- Oh, the aphrodisiac.

14:00.774 --> 14:02.709
- Looking back on it,

14:02.742 --> 14:06.146
maybe the knee was,
like, an excuse to get--

14:06.179 --> 14:07.881
remove myself
from that situation.

14:07.914 --> 14:09.883
I never had cameras
in my face before.

14:09.916 --> 14:11.117
It was all
very overwhelming.

14:11.151 --> 14:14.521
So obviously, there wasn't
a knee problem,

14:14.554 --> 14:15.722
because I got an MRI.
- Did you not feel like you--

14:15.755 --> 14:19.292
you were returning to an even
more stressful situation

14:19.325 --> 14:22.062
than you had left?
- Yeah. Yeah, I ----ed myself.

14:22.062 --> 14:24.531
Yeah, I didn't--
It wasn't a plan, you know?

14:24.564 --> 14:26.933
- Clearly.
- Yeah.

14:26.966 --> 14:29.836
- Captain Sandy, Wendy R. said,
"I understand you wanting

14:29.869 --> 14:33.206
"to give Matt another shot
after his 'knee injury,'

14:33.239 --> 14:35.108
"but it was really hard
to watch you let him

14:35.141 --> 14:36.910
"return to the boat
yet again

14:36.943 --> 14:40.113
"after his drunken departure
in the middle of the night.

14:40.146 --> 14:41.715
Why keep him..."
- That's not fair.

14:41.748 --> 14:43.683
- "After two strikes
when there was another chef

14:43.717 --> 14:44.951
waiting in the wings?"

14:44.984 --> 14:46.486
-It's a big job
being a chef.

14:46.519 --> 14:47.887
I'm not making
excuses for him,

14:47.921 --> 14:50.657
but I had to make
a decision.

14:50.690 --> 14:53.526
It's better to go with who
I know than who I don't know.

14:53.560 --> 14:56.363
- And by the way,
how did Matt's food

14:56.396 --> 14:58.431
compare to other chefs
you've worked with,

14:58.465 --> 15:00.600
Katie and Sandy?

15:00.633 --> 15:02.402
- He never--
no one ever complained.

15:02.435 --> 15:05.038
- It was just consistently good.
Yeah, it was always--

15:05.038 --> 15:07.707
the way it tasted.
It always came out hot.

15:07.741 --> 15:10.076
There was never a complaint
about a meal being too cold,

15:10.110 --> 15:12.045
which is probably one of
the most common complaints,

15:12.078 --> 15:15.181
um, on a yacht or probably
any service industry.

15:15.215 --> 15:17.817
So it really blew me away.

15:17.851 --> 15:20.453
- Char M. wants to know
if you guys would

15:20.487 --> 15:23.823
ever want to work with
Chef Mathew again.

15:23.857 --> 15:26.159
She says,
"Besides believing

15:26.192 --> 15:28.061
"he's the most important
person on the ship,

15:28.094 --> 15:30.130
"he seemed to not be
professional

15:30.163 --> 15:31.531
by walking off
as often--"

15:31.564 --> 15:33.500
So everybody's
raising their hands.

15:33.533 --> 15:35.068
Everybody would work
with him again.

15:35.068 --> 15:37.337
Sandy is not
raising her hand.

15:37.370 --> 15:40.707
- I like reliability
and dependability.

15:40.740 --> 15:44.077
Matthew's a great guy,
but I just--

15:44.077 --> 15:45.812
and after watching the show--
- She's judging me

15:45.845 --> 15:48.081
on two days in my life.
- After watching the show,

15:48.081 --> 15:52.185
People who poke the bear--
it's-it's a little hard.

15:52.218 --> 15:54.654
So, um, with everything
that happened--

15:54.688 --> 15:56.222
you know, I don't
see everything.

15:56.256 --> 15:58.591
So when I watch the show,
I'm just--

15:58.625 --> 16:00.260
I was actually mortified.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.062
- Why are you judging me?
I work year round.

16:02.095 --> 16:03.630
- Well, she's judging you
on what you said

16:03.663 --> 16:05.031
and how you behaved.
- She's a big phony, Andy.

16:05.031 --> 16:07.367
- That's why.
There's your answer.

16:07.400 --> 16:10.337
- It's hard to put words
back in your mouth though, Mat.

16:10.370 --> 16:12.138
I mean, she said
she's judging you

16:12.172 --> 16:14.374
based on things she
saw you do and say.

16:14.407 --> 16:16.242
- Yeah, but-- I know, but--
yeah, whatever.

16:16.276 --> 16:18.244
- An editor can't
create those things.

16:18.278 --> 16:22.082
Do you think they made you look
worse than you were as a chef?

16:22.115 --> 16:25.051
- I mean, like,
I did everything I did.

16:25.085 --> 16:27.253
I regret the bad
moments I have,

16:27.287 --> 16:29.923
but I think
I'm-I'm a good employee,

16:29.956 --> 16:32.192
and I think Sandy's
one of the worst captains

16:32.225 --> 16:34.527
I've ever worked with
in my 15 years on boats.

16:34.561 --> 16:36.296
- Okay, like, wait.
I think that's a bit--

16:36.329 --> 16:38.665
slightly too far, Mathew.
Like, I think--

16:38.698 --> 16:41.067
what the problem is-
- Well, that was the truth.

16:41.101 --> 16:43.269
- No, I think the issue was,
like, obviously Captain Sandy's

16:43.303 --> 16:45.105
now seeing everything that
happened on the nights out

16:45.138 --> 16:47.574
and stuff, and, like,
for unreliability,

16:47.607 --> 16:49.642
I understand from a captain's
point of it--

16:49.676 --> 16:51.878
point of view, like,
it's hard to employee somebody

16:51.911 --> 16:54.414
when they're, like,
unreliable and, like, they quit.

16:54.447 --> 16:56.850
That's all-- like, that-that's
the in-in that--

16:56.883 --> 16:58.885
in that respect, I agree.
Like, it-it-it's hard--

16:58.918 --> 17:00.186
it must be hard
for her to think

17:00.220 --> 17:02.322
that she would employ you again
if you're gonna quit.

17:02.355 --> 17:04.724
- And you're not always
gonna see eye-to-eye.

17:04.758 --> 17:06.326
- Yeah. Yeah, you're not always
gonna see eye-to-eye.

17:06.359 --> 17:08.561
- You can be
really great at your job,

17:08.595 --> 17:11.865
but there's another side
that comes to our job,

17:11.898 --> 17:13.566
and that's personality.

17:13.600 --> 17:17.270
We have to be able
to defuse things

17:17.303 --> 17:18.938
because we live
and work together,

17:19.039 --> 17:21.307
and it's-it's not easy
all the time.

17:21.341 --> 17:23.710
And then you add alcohol,
and people do and say things

17:23.743 --> 17:25.478
that they don't mean
and they regret,

17:25.512 --> 17:27.881
and, you know,
when I watched the show,

17:27.914 --> 17:30.050
I was just like,
"Oh, my God." Like--

17:30.083 --> 17:31.418
- Yeah, how do you
think I felt?

17:31.451 --> 17:33.153
- You know, I think
it's hard when people--

17:33.186 --> 17:35.422
if you do a constructive
criticism,

17:35.455 --> 17:37.657
some people can't take that,
and you--

17:37.691 --> 17:39.926
you just don't know
when to not talk,

17:39.959 --> 17:41.561
and that-that's
your Achilles heel

17:41.594 --> 17:43.063
is your own self.

17:43.096 --> 17:46.232
- Okay.
- Up next..

17:46.266 --> 17:48.768
r behavior
in general was quite sh--.
is your own self.

17:48.802 --> 17:50.937
- If anything, she was
edited nicely that night.

17:50.970 --> 17:52.806
She was much worse.

17:52.839 --> 17:54.207
- Production actually
stepped in

18:05.585 --> 18:06.252
- One of Lexi's
go-to insults

18:07.520 --> 18:09.122
was to remind everyone

18:09.155 --> 18:11.725
she had more money
in her bank account.

18:11.758 --> 18:14.361
But during one fateful
hot tub night on deck,

18:14.394 --> 18:16.863
her antics left
the crew's patience

18:16.896 --> 18:20.066
totally overdrawn.
Watch.

18:28.875 --> 18:30.276
- Why does she always
talk about money?

18:30.310 --> 18:34.080
She's like, "You're so poor!
You're so poor!"

18:44.524 --> 18:46.059
- I'm ----ing being
inappropriate?

18:46.092 --> 18:48.061
But I feel as if you're
being inappropriate,

18:48.094 --> 18:49.129
so (BLEEP) you.

18:49.162 --> 18:50.530
- I'm not the one that was
offended like you!

18:50.563 --> 18:51.931
- Shut up!
- Oh, you kiss ass!

18:51.965 --> 18:53.433
- Me?
- And you're fake as (BLEEP).

18:53.466 --> 18:56.236
You're a ----ing Bosun!
Stand the (BLEEP) down!

18:56.269 --> 18:58.972
David, you're so whack.
- Aren't you like unemployable?

18:59.072 --> 19:01.341
- No, I'm employable 'cause
I have more money than you.

19:01.374 --> 19:04.244
- You're talking sh--.
- Lexi? Lexi?

19:04.277 --> 19:06.246
- Katie, you're a Capricorn, and
you can feel what I'm feeling.

19:06.279 --> 19:08.248
(BLEEP) her being a kiss ass!
(BLEEP) off!

19:08.281 --> 19:09.649
- Hey!
[screaming]

19:09.683 --> 19:12.352
- You made some really personal
inappropriate comments,

19:12.385 --> 19:13.620
and not just to me.

19:13.653 --> 19:15.088
You owe an apology
to Zee as well.

19:15.121 --> 19:17.424
- Yes, I apologize,
Katie and David,

19:17.457 --> 19:19.759
for my stuff last night.

19:19.793 --> 19:22.929
- I feel like you guys
can figure this out.

19:23.029 --> 19:25.065
- I'm pissed off
with you again

19:25.098 --> 19:27.600
because it doesn't feel
like you want to be here.

19:27.634 --> 19:30.036
It doesn't feel
like you care, really.

19:30.070 --> 19:32.439
- No, I don't care.
I'm leaving.

19:32.472 --> 19:35.608
- Maybe this isn't
the right environment for her.

19:35.642 --> 19:38.778
- I'm just gonna ask you
to give her another chance.

19:38.812 --> 19:42.482
You're a leader.
Rise. Go lead.

19:42.515 --> 19:45.051
[nervous chuckling]

19:45.051 --> 19:46.853
- Okay, I-I will say--

19:46.886 --> 19:48.788
So I want to start
with you, Sandy.

19:48.822 --> 19:50.623
I'm mean, you're-you're
watching yourself say,

19:50.657 --> 19:52.826
"You can figure this out.
Give it another chance."

19:52.859 --> 19:55.595
Now you're seeing the show,
and you're seeing footage

19:55.628 --> 19:58.365
that you hadn't seen before.

19:58.398 --> 20:00.834
What would you
have done differently,

20:00.867 --> 20:03.103
or would you have done
anything differently?

20:03.136 --> 20:05.138
- The reality is,
I don't see everything.

20:05.171 --> 20:06.773
I never heard specifics,

20:06.806 --> 20:08.641
so if someone
comes up to you and says,

20:08.675 --> 20:10.243
"It was bad.
It was real bad."

20:10.276 --> 20:12.545
Do you base firing someone
off of that?

20:12.579 --> 20:15.382
I didn't see
Lexi's behavior.

20:15.415 --> 20:16.983
So if I would have seen it,

20:17.017 --> 20:19.986
um, I would have fired her
immediately.

20:20.020 --> 20:23.223
- So, Zee, then what was going
through your mind

20:23.256 --> 20:25.525
when she pushed you
in the crew mess?

20:25.558 --> 20:26.860
- You know, I'm gonna
step in here.

20:26.893 --> 20:29.262
Production actually
stepped in and--

20:29.295 --> 20:32.599
- They-they did?
- Yeah, because it was

20:32.632 --> 20:34.401
getting so out of hand.
- Yeah. They did. They did.

20:34.434 --> 20:36.569
- They actually stepped in
and like, lost our sh--,

20:36.603 --> 20:38.271
and was like, "This is not
what we're about,"

20:38.304 --> 20:39.839
and if it goes any further,
I'm pretty sure

20:39.873 --> 20:42.008
Lexi would have been
removed straight away.

20:42.042 --> 20:45.378
Um, but I guess
she reigned it in at that point.

20:45.412 --> 20:48.281
- If anything, she was edited
nicely that night.

20:48.314 --> 20:49.883
- I think so, too.

20:49.916 --> 20:52.652
- She was much worse.
- I completely understand

20:52.686 --> 20:54.554
that grief is, like,
such a horrible thing,

20:54.587 --> 20:57.891
and, like, you-you know,
everyone, uh, deals with it

20:57.924 --> 20:59.793
in a different way, and I
completely understand that,

20:59.826 --> 21:03.196
but at no point do I think that
it means that you should be,

21:03.229 --> 21:05.899
um, that offensive
to another person

21:05.932 --> 21:08.234
and that aggressive
to another person.

21:08.268 --> 21:11.271
And I feel like, yeah,
that-- to-to me,

21:11.304 --> 21:12.605
that just-- it's not--
it's not--

21:12.639 --> 21:14.174
it's not really an excuse.

21:14.207 --> 21:16.176
- Courtney, knowing
that your dad

21:16.209 --> 21:18.211
is-is going through it
right now,

21:18.244 --> 21:20.513
and that you are,
uh, with him,

21:20.547 --> 21:22.248
could you empathize

21:22.282 --> 21:25.185
with Lexi's state
of mind at all?

21:25.218 --> 21:29.255
- Uh, no. I'm-- I--
My dad's now in a home.

21:29.289 --> 21:32.659
And I-- he doesn't
remember who I am.

21:32.692 --> 21:34.294
And I still would never
act that way

21:34.327 --> 21:36.296
against another
person ever.

21:36.329 --> 21:39.599
- I am really sorry to hear
about your dad, Courtney.

21:39.632 --> 21:41.601
- We're all there for you.
You know that.

21:41.634 --> 21:45.238
- It was hard, because I was
concerned about Lexi.

21:45.271 --> 21:47.707
I actually pulled her aside
and spoke to her and said,

21:47.741 --> 21:49.309
"Do you think this
is the environment

21:49.342 --> 21:51.711
"you should be in?
Because I as your Chief Stew

21:51.745 --> 21:53.380
"do not think you should
be here right now

21:53.413 --> 21:56.116
"because mentally,
you're going through a lot,

21:56.116 --> 21:58.351
"and it-- I don't know
if this is how you deal

21:58.385 --> 22:01.054
"with grief, you know,
but I don't think

22:01.054 --> 22:03.189
this is the best environment
for you right now."

22:03.223 --> 22:05.759
- Wow. All right.
We gotta move on.

22:05.792 --> 22:09.195
Chef Mat and Lexi
had their first dustup

22:09.229 --> 22:11.297
over a dirt pile.

22:11.331 --> 22:13.500
But as the charter season
went on,

22:13.533 --> 22:16.536
these two Yachties
couldn't stop slinging mud

22:16.569 --> 22:18.471
in each other's direction.

22:18.505 --> 22:19.606
Take a look.

22:19.639 --> 22:21.408
- Can you please not step
in that? I just swept it.

22:21.441 --> 22:23.109
- I will sweep it up.

22:23.143 --> 22:25.278
Just focus on putting
the lamb on the plate.

22:25.311 --> 22:26.813
- You can't talk to me
like you're the boss.

22:26.846 --> 22:28.615
I'm in charge of the galley,
all right? Never again.

22:28.648 --> 22:30.517
I've never disliked someone
more in my life.

22:30.550 --> 22:32.686
- You're a nobody.
You're a low life.

22:43.363 --> 22:44.431
- She had bad parents.

22:44.464 --> 22:45.265
- Your parents should have
----ing aborted you.

22:45.298 --> 22:46.866
- Ohh.
- Yeah, and if this wasn't

22:46.900 --> 22:48.601
on camera, I woulda
smacked your ass.

22:48.635 --> 22:51.705
- I'm just gonna tell Sandy
it's either me or her tomorrow.

22:51.738 --> 22:53.707
- Who started it?
- Mathew.

22:53.740 --> 22:55.709
He says stuff
to get under my skin.

22:55.742 --> 22:58.111
- She told me I should have been
aborted multiple times.

22:58.144 --> 22:59.245
- If Mathew says
something to you,

22:59.279 --> 23:01.781
your reaction, Lexi, goes
to a whole 'nother level.

23:01.815 --> 23:04.184
- What I'm hearing
is that you are difficult

23:04.217 --> 23:07.487
to live with.
- Well, he said last night

23:07.520 --> 23:09.089
that he's gonna give you
an ultimatum--

23:09.122 --> 23:11.358
either him or me.
- If you give me an ultimatum,

23:11.391 --> 23:13.093
you can walk--
pack your ----ing sh--

23:13.126 --> 23:15.128
and walk off the boat.
That's how a I feel.

23:15.161 --> 23:17.964
The many
outweigh the one.

23:18.064 --> 23:21.167
And I-I have to make
a hard decision.

23:21.201 --> 23:22.736
I have to let you go.

23:22.769 --> 23:24.471
Lexi crossed the line,

23:24.504 --> 23:25.772
and if I have one person

23:25.805 --> 23:28.675
that's disturbing
the entire crew,

23:28.708 --> 23:30.076
I need to let go
of that person.

23:30.110 --> 23:32.278
- You are replaceable.

23:32.312 --> 23:34.080
There's someone sitting
in quarantine right now

23:34.114 --> 23:36.516
to take your job.

23:36.549 --> 23:39.919
- Lex, need a hand?

23:39.953 --> 23:42.455
- Mat, Kelly from
North Carolina said,

23:42.489 --> 23:44.090
"After looking back
at the season,

23:44.090 --> 23:45.525
"did Chef Mathew realize

23:45.558 --> 23:47.627
"he's just as much
as fault--

23:47.660 --> 23:49.929
"at fault
as Lexi was?

23:49.963 --> 23:51.931
"She's not perfect,
but you were clearly trying

23:51.965 --> 23:53.767
"to get a reaction from her."

23:53.800 --> 23:55.568
- Yeah, I mean,
there was so much--

23:55.602 --> 23:57.604
I-I blame it on
the alcohol involved.

23:57.637 --> 23:59.139
The tour guide was
feeding us alcohol.

23:59.172 --> 24:01.041
It was a-- yeah.

24:01.041 --> 24:02.909
I'm not proud
of that fight with her

24:02.942 --> 24:04.644
and ruining everyone's
day off.

24:04.678 --> 24:07.447
And, like, we had
a challenging relationship

24:07.480 --> 24:08.948
on the boat
working together,

24:09.049 --> 24:10.617
but I don't want
to say anything

24:10.650 --> 24:13.520
