24:37.077 --> 24:40.347
whereas Lexi didn't actually
apologize to anybody sincerely.

24:40.380 --> 24:41.748
Me and Lexi were
literally friends

24:41.781 --> 24:43.183
at the start of the season.

24:43.216 --> 24:45.085
Like, we were friends.

24:45.118 --> 24:48.421
- We all got along.
Our first charter was great.

24:48.455 --> 24:49.756
- We all got along.
It was just the fact

24:49.789 --> 24:51.091
that what happened
after that

24:51.091 --> 24:54.928
was like a roller coaster
of sh--.

24:54.961 --> 24:56.262
- I'm curious what you think.

24:56.296 --> 25:00.133
Lexi on social media
has really been, um,

25:00.166 --> 25:02.869
blaming a lot of people.

25:02.902 --> 25:04.471
She's been blaming
production.

25:04.504 --> 25:07.540
She says she's been given
a very bad edit.

25:07.574 --> 25:10.577
She thinks she's been edited
very unfairly.

25:10.610 --> 25:13.046
- That's pretty classic of
anyone throughout the seasons

25:13.046 --> 25:14.914
who's come on "Below Deck"

25:14.948 --> 25:17.951
and not liked the way that
they've behaved when drunk.

25:18.051 --> 25:20.820
You know, it's pretty nasty
when you watch yourself back

25:20.854 --> 25:23.156
and you see all the regrets
and mistakes you've made.

25:23.189 --> 25:25.925
It's not the edit.
It's you.

25:25.959 --> 25:28.528
- Lloyd, what do you think?

25:28.561 --> 25:30.096
- We-we all gave her
a second chance.

25:30.130 --> 25:32.599
I went in there with
a fresh, uh, face.

25:32.632 --> 25:33.667
So did the other deck boys

25:33.700 --> 25:35.802
when we spent that time
in the hot tub.

25:35.835 --> 25:37.404
Um, and as far
as we were concerned,

25:37.437 --> 25:39.406
we were gonna try and get on
with the rest of the season.

25:39.439 --> 25:40.840
And then she-she went

25:40.874 --> 25:43.476
off the-
off the rails again.

25:43.510 --> 25:45.345
Uh, and-and enough
is enough.

25:45.378 --> 25:48.081
- Zee, did she get
a bad edit?

25:48.081 --> 25:49.549
- Um, no, honestly,
I do not believe

25:49.582 --> 25:51.518
Lexi got an unfair edit.

25:51.551 --> 25:54.220
Like, I know she recorded
a whole bunch of things

25:54.254 --> 25:56.556
on Instagram
which are not fair

25:56.589 --> 25:59.693
in terms of production
and in terms of myself.

25:59.726 --> 26:01.895
She didn't get an unfair edit,
I don't think.

26:01.928 --> 26:03.329
- What has she
shared about you

26:03.363 --> 26:06.232
that-that you've
taken issue with?

26:06.266 --> 26:08.201
- I mean, apparently, I-

26:08.234 --> 26:10.303
apparently I want
to be white,

26:10.337 --> 26:13.940
and that I don't-
I don't support Black people.

26:14.040 --> 26:15.942
That's really not something
that I believe at all,

26:16.042 --> 26:19.245
only because I advocate
for Black empowerment

26:19.279 --> 26:21.581
and Black people
doing great things,

26:21.614 --> 26:23.583
so just generally,

26:23.616 --> 26:26.252
her behavior in general
was honestly quite sh--.

26:26.286 --> 26:27.754
You don't treat
people that you care about

26:27.787 --> 26:29.856
or you don't treat
people like that.

26:29.889 --> 26:32.292
- Wow. Up next...

26:32.325 --> 26:34.327
- From the get-go,
it wasn't--

26:34.361 --> 26:35.929
It was a sh--show,
basically.

26:35.962 --> 26:38.732
I was so ----ing over
this sh--.

26:50.610 --> 26:51.344
Well, you've heard
of Chief Stews,

26:52.178 --> 26:53.513
but we're now being joined

26:53.546 --> 26:57.250
by Lady Michelle's
brief Stew, Delaney.

26:57.283 --> 27:00.320
Hi, Delaney.
- Hey, guys.

27:00.353 --> 27:03.823
- Uh, well, when Delaney
triggered a crew cabin swap

27:03.857 --> 27:07.794
that was a like a bad game
of crew-sical chairs,

27:07.827 --> 27:10.030
Katie ended her time
on board

27:10.063 --> 27:12.799
with an abrupt
record scratch.

27:12.832 --> 27:16.302
But did Delaney
face the music too soon?

27:16.336 --> 27:18.138
Watch this.

27:18.171 --> 27:20.306
- Hi! Katie.
- D-Delaney.

27:20.340 --> 27:22.042
So I've never been
a Stewardess before.

27:22.042 --> 27:24.144
Um, yeah.

27:24.177 --> 27:25.612
- Management
just called.

27:25.645 --> 27:28.948
We can not allow
cabin sharing

27:29.049 --> 27:31.051
between a male and a female.
- Okay.

27:31.051 --> 27:33.887
Every single crew member
is gonna have to shuffle cabins

27:33.920 --> 27:35.822
to make this work.

27:35.855 --> 27:37.791
- Yeah, let's do it.
I lost my cabin.

27:37.824 --> 27:40.060
- I'm just ----ing over
thinking about this.

27:40.060 --> 27:41.327
It's just causing
too much drama,

27:41.361 --> 27:43.063
and I feel so sick.

27:43.063 --> 27:44.197
- I actually got
another girl on,

27:44.230 --> 27:46.066
because Lexi couldn't
do her ----ing job,

27:46.066 --> 27:49.069
and now they're both doing
the same job together.

27:49.069 --> 27:50.337
- I'm just being lazy.
- I don't want

27:50.370 --> 27:52.739
that girl to be here.
- I know that.

27:52.772 --> 27:54.674
I feel terrible saying this,

27:54.708 --> 27:56.643
but I think
it would be best

27:56.676 --> 27:58.278
if you finish
this trip

27:58.311 --> 28:02.315
and we say goodbye.
- Do I think it's fair? No.

28:02.349 --> 28:05.352
- Can you get Lexi's luggage?
I just let her go.

28:05.385 --> 28:07.854
Considering Delaney
is still here,

28:07.887 --> 28:09.189
it's an option.

28:09.222 --> 28:11.891
She's not a Stew, but at least
you have another person.

28:11.925 --> 28:14.494
- I'd so much rather,
like, work harder

28:14.527 --> 28:15.762
and work longer

28:15.795 --> 28:17.897
than have
the emotional stress

28:17.931 --> 28:20.900
of bringing somebody new in
or bringing Delaney back.

28:20.934 --> 28:22.502
- It's around the clock
for deck crew.

28:22.535 --> 28:25.338
We're helping with laundry,
with service.

28:25.372 --> 28:28.208
It's been a lot.
- Hello?

28:28.241 --> 28:29.609
Sister Katie?

28:29.642 --> 28:31.611
- A guest in the hot tub
needs some drinks.

28:31.644 --> 28:34.047
- It's ----ing stupid, because,
like, a couple weeks ago,

28:34.047 --> 28:35.849
I'm complaining about
needing more Stews,

28:35.882 --> 28:38.518
and now I'm like,
"Hey, let's just fire two Stews

28:38.551 --> 28:39.419
"and just keep two."

28:39.452 --> 28:42.489
Like, what is wrong with me?

28:42.522 --> 28:43.590
- Krista L. wants to know

28:43.623 --> 28:45.825
your first impressions
of Delaney.

28:45.859 --> 28:48.862
Did you think she was gonna
fit in the group, Katie?

28:48.895 --> 28:50.764
- Um, well,
my first impression

28:50.797 --> 28:52.665
was finding out
she wasn't a Stew,

28:52.699 --> 28:54.501
so obviously,
from the get-go,

28:54.534 --> 28:58.905
it wasn't-- it was just--
it was a sh--show, basically.

28:58.938 --> 29:02.142
- Well, so talk to me about that
a little, Delaney.

29:02.175 --> 29:04.344
- Yeah, so I was
in quarantine for deck.

29:04.377 --> 29:07.080
Um, and then I found out
the need was for a Stew

29:07.113 --> 29:08.114
very last minute,

29:08.148 --> 29:09.716
so it was just as much
of a surprise to me

29:09.749 --> 29:11.317
as it was to Katie, I feel.

29:11.351 --> 29:14.020
- Matt, Carley E. said,
"With how many times

29:14.020 --> 29:16.823
"you walked out and quit, Mat,
why were you so forward

29:16.856 --> 29:19.592
"with your thoughts about
wanting Delaney off the boat?"

29:19.626 --> 29:21.227
- I only walked out
and quit once.

29:21.261 --> 29:23.863
The other one was the knee
injury/panic attack,

29:23.897 --> 29:26.066
so it was only one,
but, um,

29:26.099 --> 29:27.600
I burned my finger so bad.

29:27.634 --> 29:28.735
I was in a lot of pain.

29:28.768 --> 29:31.504
Martin's cabin was musty
and had no portholes.

29:31.538 --> 29:33.373
I just wanted
my bed back, you know?

29:33.406 --> 29:35.775
[laughter]

29:35.809 --> 29:37.143
I wanted my bed.

29:37.177 --> 29:40.347
- You know what though?
I actually did that.

29:40.380 --> 29:42.048
I said, "Can I share
a cabin with him?"

29:42.048 --> 29:44.150
Delaney was brought on
to try to help, like,

29:44.184 --> 29:45.719
figure this situation out,

29:45.752 --> 29:48.054
and it just ended up, like,
creating more drama

29:48.088 --> 29:49.389
and more stress,
so in my eyes,

29:49.422 --> 29:52.058
I was like, just can it.
Let's just, like, move on.

29:52.058 --> 29:54.794
I was so ----ing
over this sh--

29:54.828 --> 29:56.396
that I was dealing with
that season so--

29:56.429 --> 29:58.832
- She's also
not a Stew.

29:58.865 --> 30:01.501
- Do you regret
your decision, Katie?

30:01.534 --> 30:03.970
- I don't. I do
for the rest of the crew,

30:04.004 --> 30:06.806
and it wasn't-- like,
for deck crew, I do,

30:06.840 --> 30:09.042
but for everything else,
I don't.

30:09.075 --> 30:11.077
- Malia, do you wish--
given the-

30:11.111 --> 30:14.214
the pressure it put
on your team,

30:14.247 --> 30:17.317
do you wish that Katie could--
had kept her around?

30:17.350 --> 30:19.052
- You know, I-I think
having Delaney there

30:19.085 --> 30:20.754
would have been
super helpful, yes.

30:20.787 --> 30:21.721
And Delaney was.

30:21.755 --> 30:23.490
She was up for,
you know, helping out

30:23.523 --> 30:24.924
wherever she could,

30:24.958 --> 30:27.127
but I think Katie
made the decision

30:27.160 --> 30:28.595
that she thought
was best for the team,

30:28.628 --> 30:29.929
and I stand by that.

30:29.963 --> 30:31.898
- I-- what I needed
at the time--

30:31.931 --> 30:33.633
I needed a stewardess
with experience

30:33.667 --> 30:36.069
that could be thrown
straight in the deep end.

30:36.102 --> 30:38.705
Um, and Delaney
wasn't that.

30:38.738 --> 30:40.040
She's not a stewardess.

30:40.073 --> 30:42.075
She's never been
a super yacht stewardess.

30:42.108 --> 30:43.743
So it wasn't
what I needed.

30:43.777 --> 30:47.080
It wasn't Delaney.
It was not the right fit

30:47.113 --> 30:49.816
for what we were after
at that time.

30:49.849 --> 30:52.585
- Delaney, didn't you
think you would get busted?

30:52.619 --> 30:54.554
- Um, I didn't--
I did not lie on my CV.

30:54.587 --> 30:55.889
You guys are welcome
to call that captain

30:55.922 --> 30:57.724
that I did work for
for months

30:57.757 --> 30:59.492
on a small boat
in San Diego.

30:59.526 --> 31:01.061
Like, it--
none of it's a lie.

31:01.061 --> 31:02.896
It's just a small boat
Deck Stew position

31:02.929 --> 31:04.197
is not a super yacht.

31:04.230 --> 31:05.331
Frankly, I didn't really
want to be a Stew,

31:05.365 --> 31:07.534
but I rose to the occasion,
and I, you know,

31:07.567 --> 31:09.102
I did what
the opportunity was.

31:09.135 --> 31:12.772
- But a Deck Stew does
Stewardess things.

31:12.806 --> 31:14.074
I was a Deck Stew.

31:14.074 --> 31:14.974
- Yeah, and I could
make a bed,

31:15.075 --> 31:16.309
and I could do things.

31:16.343 --> 31:18.311
On smaller boats,
we don't have--

31:18.345 --> 31:19.713
- Yeah, no, I get that.
For sure.

31:19.746 --> 31:21.081
- Like, people aren't sleeping
in cabins for day charters.

31:21.081 --> 31:23.083
- Well, I just think, like,
think of it in Katie's position.

31:23.083 --> 31:24.851
She sees someone that
it says "Deck Stew,"

31:24.884 --> 31:26.619
and then we get her on,

31:26.653 --> 31:28.088
and we're like, "Hey, you're
gonna be a Stewardess."

31:28.121 --> 31:30.657
You know, then that
essentially is saying,

31:30.690 --> 31:32.258
you know, you're green.

31:32.292 --> 31:34.227
You're green in--
as a Stewardess.

31:34.260 --> 31:35.628
So that's not
very helpful.

31:35.662 --> 31:37.597
That means Katie's
gonna have to train her.

31:37.630 --> 31:39.165
And we're at the point
in the season

31:39.199 --> 31:40.834
where we don't have time
to train someone.

31:40.867 --> 31:44.771
- Well, Delaney,
so what's next for you?

31:44.804 --> 31:46.006
- Uh, I live
in Hawaii right now,

31:46.106 --> 31:47.374
and I work on
a day charter boat,

31:47.407 --> 31:49.676
and, um,
it's a lot of fun.

31:49.709 --> 31:50.910
- Sounds like everything
worked out

31:50.944 --> 31:53.179
just peachy for you.

31:53.213 --> 31:55.548
Okay, well, I'm about to say
goodbye to Delaney

31:55.582 --> 31:56.616
and also Lloyd.

31:56.649 --> 31:58.785
It sounds like you're
about to lose service

31:58.818 --> 31:59.886
on your ship,

31:59.919 --> 32:01.921
so I want to say goodbye
to you, uh,

32:01.955 --> 32:03.556
before you get
cut off.

32:03.590 --> 32:05.358
Is there any-anything
you want to say

32:05.392 --> 32:07.660
before we say
goodbye to you, Lloyd?

32:07.694 --> 32:08.795
- Um, I just want to say

32:08.828 --> 32:11.197
it's so good to be back with
the-the crew again.

32:11.231 --> 32:14.067
Uh, I mean,
we all keep in touch.

32:14.100 --> 32:17.303
Uh, it's nice to have you
all in one place

32:17.337 --> 32:19.739
rather than speaking
individually on the phone.

32:19.773 --> 32:23.677
[audio breaking up]

32:23.710 --> 32:25.478
- Aw, we're

32:25.512 --> 32:26.413
- Love you, Lloyd.

32:26.446 --> 32:28.481
- Love you, Lloyd!

32:28.515 --> 32:30.183
- We'll do another
group chat soon, Lloyd.

32:30.216 --> 32:31.985
- Bye, Lloyd.
- Hearts and lungs.

32:32.085 --> 32:35.588
- See you later,
and thank you, Delaney.

32:35.622 --> 32:36.790
- See you later.

32:36.823 --> 32:38.091
- It was very nice to meet
all you guys,

32:38.124 --> 32:39.793
and I wish you guys the best
in your careers and yachting,

32:39.826 --> 32:41.728
and hopefully see you
around sometime.

32:41.761 --> 32:42.729
- All right.
- You, too.

32:42.762 --> 32:43.697
- Thank you, Delaney.
Thank you.

32:43.730 --> 32:46.800
- Thanks, Delaney.
- You, too, Delaney.

32:46.833 --> 32:48.435
- Courtney's
pouring her wine.

32:48.468 --> 32:50.103
- They call her
Coco Loco.

32:50.103 --> 32:51.705
- We'll be back.

32:51.738 --> 32:52.706
Coming up...

32:52.739 --> 32:55.108
- She should have told me.
- Did you realize

32:55.108 --> 32:57.811
you were losing
Captain Sandy's trust?

33:08.088 --> 33:08.955
- In seasons past,
Captain Sandy and Malia

33:10.890 --> 33:12.325
never struggled
with keeping

33:12.359 --> 33:15.428
their professional
relationship afloat.

33:15.462 --> 33:18.164
But this season,
trust issues between the two

33:18.198 --> 33:21.735
caused their partnership
to rapidly take on water.

33:21.768 --> 33:24.537
Watch.

33:27.073 --> 33:28.308
- I just asked Dave,

33:28.341 --> 33:30.343
but that's looking
like he didn't.

33:37.684 --> 33:39.519
- I'm not stupid.
She's covering.

33:39.552 --> 33:41.921
But in no way does
Malia get to dictate

33:41.955 --> 33:44.424
what is told to me,
and what isn't told to me.

33:44.457 --> 33:45.959
I need the trust.

33:45.992 --> 33:48.361
- They weren't tight.
- No.

33:48.395 --> 33:50.196
- Is there a plastic bag?
- No.

33:50.230 --> 33:53.733
- That's planting a little
seed of doubt in my mind.

33:53.767 --> 33:55.902
[yelling]

33:55.935 --> 33:57.604
[gasping]
- Dave!

33:57.637 --> 33:59.406
Are you okay?
- No.

33:59.439 --> 34:01.207
I'll do the forward ones.
- Can you?

34:01.241 --> 34:02.776
- Yeah.
- I don't know that

34:02.809 --> 34:04.844
I can put you over,
knowing that you're injured.

34:04.878 --> 34:06.379
- Tell me why
you're limping.

34:06.413 --> 34:08.815
- I fell.

34:08.848 --> 34:10.684
- Why wasn't it
reported to me?

34:10.717 --> 34:13.186
You, I'm really
disappointed in.

34:13.219 --> 34:14.788
It's a ----ing incident.

34:14.821 --> 34:16.723
The fact that Malia
knew about his injury

34:16.756 --> 34:19.325
is not okay with me.
She broke my trust.

34:19.359 --> 34:20.794
No.
- I'm not a chief officer.

34:20.827 --> 34:21.928
- I don't give a (BLEEP)!

34:21.961 --> 34:24.164
You should have come to me
that he was hurt!

34:24.197 --> 34:25.932
- I didn't know it was that--
- Stop making excuses!

34:25.965 --> 34:27.334
I don't trust you!
I can't trust you.

34:27.367 --> 34:29.803
- Okay, okay.

34:30.603 --> 34:32.706
- Okay, uh.

34:32.739 --> 34:34.741
Sandy, Stacey K.
wants to know

34:34.774 --> 34:37.577
why you got so frustrated
when Malia didn't immediately

34:37.610 --> 34:42.115
throw her crew under
the bus about the jetski.

34:42.148 --> 34:43.483
- Because--
- Um, Stacey K. thinks

34:43.516 --> 34:44.884
that makes her
a good manager

34:44.918 --> 34:47.620
to wait and see,
and she thought

34:47.654 --> 34:49.989
that was out of
character for you.

34:50.090 --> 34:53.760
- Malia-- my expectation
for Malia is really high.

34:53.793 --> 34:56.996
I don't have that expectation
for the deckhands

34:57.097 --> 34:58.732
like I do for Malia.

34:58.765 --> 35:01.434
Um...

35:01.468 --> 35:02.936
she should
have told me.

35:03.036 --> 35:06.406
- Did you realize you were
losing Captain Sandy's trust?

35:06.439 --> 35:08.074
- Well, I just wanna
get one thing straight.

35:08.108 --> 35:10.276
I actually wasn't
covering for David.

35:10.310 --> 35:12.245
I hadn't spoken
to him yet.

35:12.278 --> 35:14.414
So I'm not about
to tell the Captain

35:14.447 --> 35:16.082
that David left
the plugs out

35:16.116 --> 35:18.351
if I don't know.
Like, if I--

35:18.385 --> 35:20.286
and to be-- you know,
Captain Sandy was only

35:20.320 --> 35:22.689
working with the information
that she had, and I was only

35:22.722 --> 35:24.924
working with
the information that I had,

35:24.958 --> 35:27.627
and a few minutes later,
it all got resolved,

35:27.660 --> 35:30.296
so I wasn't about to
throw him under the bus.

35:30.330 --> 35:31.931
- Did you realize
at that moment

35:31.965 --> 35:35.168
by not saying something,
you were leading her to believe

35:35.201 --> 35:37.504
you were covering
for someone,

35:37.537 --> 35:40.440
and thereby causing
a trust issue between

35:40.473 --> 35:42.509
the two of you?
- No, I didn't.

35:42.542 --> 35:45.211
And had I realized that,
it would, you know,

35:45.245 --> 35:48.448
come off as me being
untrusting, or, like,

35:48.481 --> 35:50.583
trying to lie or cover.
I would have just said

35:50.617 --> 35:53.853
"I don't know yet."
Like, "I don't know."

35:53.887 --> 35:56.322
- Sometimes when you get that
little mustard seed of doubt,

35:56.356 --> 35:57.991
you go, "Wow,
I never wanna doubt

35:58.091 --> 36:00.794
"that she will never
tell me the truth."

36:00.827 --> 36:01.861
And that happened
in that split second,

36:01.895 --> 36:04.197
but, you know, it's--
it was the end

36:04.230 --> 36:07.233
of the charter season,
we're all exhausted,

36:07.267 --> 36:09.536
um, and...

36:09.569 --> 36:12.072
you're an excellent
bosun, period.

36:12.105 --> 36:13.840
- Thank you.

36:13.873 --> 36:15.575
- Tanya V. said,
"Malia, what did you think

36:15.608 --> 36:18.411
"when Captain Sandy
asked to see David's injury?

36:18.445 --> 36:19.646
"And do you
have any regrets

36:19.679 --> 36:22.349
"about how you initially
handled the situation?"

36:24.784 --> 36:26.653
- I think Captain Sandy
has every right to ask

36:26.686 --> 36:28.421
about David's injury.
She's the Captain,

36:28.455 --> 36:30.056
and she should have
been informed.

36:30.090 --> 36:33.393
I regret that we didn't
think of-- to go to her sooner.

36:33.426 --> 36:36.596
You know, again, this was
just a miscommunication.

36:36.629 --> 36:38.365
Like, it happened on
a drunken night off,

36:38.398 --> 36:40.400
and by the time we saw
Captain Sandy again,

36:40.433 --> 36:41.668
it was two days later,

36:41.701 --> 36:43.903
